"title": "5544: soldiers",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5544",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Active members of an army, whatever their rank. Paul uses the term frequently in his letters to draw attention to the fact that believers are engaged in spiritual warfare.</p>\n<h2>Armies of soldiers under different commanders</h2>\n<h3>Moses' soldiers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:27-Num31:28\">NUM 31:27–31:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:32\">NUM 31:32</a></p>\n<h3>Joshua's soldiers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:10-Josh8:19\">JOS 8:10–8:19</a></p>\n<h3>Abimelech's soldiers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:34-Judg9:35\">JDG 9:34–9:35</a></p>\n<h3>Benjamin's soldiers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:14-Judg20:16\">JDG 20:14–20:16</a></p>\n<h3>Philistine soldiers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:5\">1SA 13:5</a></p>\n<h3>Saul's soldiers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:22\">1SA 13:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:4\">1SA 15:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:15\">1SA 15:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:21\">1SA 15:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:7\">1SA 26:7</a></p>\n<h3>Hadadezer's soldiers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:4\">2SA 8:4</a></p>\n<h3>Aramean soldiers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam10:6\">2SA 10:6</a></p>\n<h3>Jehoahaz' soldiers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs13:7\">2KI 13:7</a></p>\n<h3>David's soldiers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:23\">2SA 3:23</a> <em>David's soldiers under Joab</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:8-2Sam23:39\">2SA 23:8–23:39</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:10-1Chr11:47\">1CH 11:10–11:47</a> <em>David's mighty men</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:1-2Sam24:9\">2SA 24:1–24:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:1-1Chr21:16\">1CH 21:1–21:16</a> <em>David displeased the LORD by counting his fighting men</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:23-1Chr12:38\">1CH 12:23–12:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr27:1-1Chr27:22\">1CH 27:1–27:22</a></p>\n<h3>Zedekiah's soldiers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:5\">2KI 25:5</a></p>\n<h3>Babylonian soldiers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer41:3\">JER 41:3</a></p>\n<h2>Individual soldiers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:1\">2KI 5:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:28\">1SA 14:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr17:17\">2CH 17:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:20-Dan3:22\">DAN 3:20–3:22</a></p>\n<h2>Soldiers came to John the Baptist</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:14\">LUK 3:14</a></p>\n<h2>Soldiers involved in the last events of Jesus Christ's life on earth</h2>\n<h3>In his arrest and trial</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:11\">LUK 23:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:36\">LUK 23:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:3\">JHN 18:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:12\">JHN 18:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:2\">JHN 19:2</a></p>\n<h3>In his crucifixion</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:27\">MAT 27:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:16\">JHN 19:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:23-John19:24\">JHN 19:23–19:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:32-John19:34\">JHN 19:32–19:34</a></p>\n<h3>After his crucifixion</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:65-Matt27:66\">MAT 27:65–27:66</a></p>\n<h3>After his resurrection</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:2-Matt28:4\">MAT 28:2–28:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:12\">MAT 28:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:15\">MAT 28:15</a></p>\n<h2>Soldiers involved in the lives of the apostles</h2>\n<h3>Peter</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:4\">ACT 12:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:6\">ACT 12:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:18\">ACT 12:18</a></p>\n<h3>Paul</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:32\">ACT 21:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:35\">ACT 21:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:37\">ACT 21:37</a></p>\n<h2>Soldiers used metaphorically</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:27\">EZK 27:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:20\">EZK 39:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:7\">JOL 2:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:15-Amos2:16\">AMO 2:15–2:16</a></p>\n<h2>Paul draws parallels between a soldier and a Christian</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:7\">1CO 9:7</a></strong> <em>An apostle has a right to be supported in material things by those to whom he preaches.</em></p>\n<h3>Christians are called fellow-soldiers</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:25\">PHP 2:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:2\">PHM 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>Christians must put Jesus Christ first</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:3-2Tim2:4\">2TI 2:3–2:4</a></strong></p>\n<h2>God as the commander of an army of soldiers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:8\">PSA 89:8</a></strong> <em>The term here translated “LORD God Almighty” can be translated “LORD God of hosts” or “LORD God of armies”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:10\">1KI 19:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:14\">JER 5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:5\">HOS 12:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:13\">AMO 4:13</a></p>",
